result.execSummary:
The defendant William F. St Germaine was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court obligations are converted to clerk of court collect.  Financial information needs to be obtained from DOC for any applicable adjustments.  No payments have been received from DOC to the Clerk of Court.
Notice of right to seek postconviction relief.

Defendant William F. St. Germaine in court with attorney Joel Kenneth Larimore.  Defendant William F. St. Germaine in custody.  Bruce Robert Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Parties do not object to appearance of Judge John Anderson by video from Bayfield County.  
Probation has been revoked.  
Atty Poquette makes statement, notes DE has credit for 72 days time served.  Parties do not have agreement, but State does not object to one year county jail.
Court asks if any victims are in the courtroom- there are none present.
Atty Larimore makes statement, agrees with DOC recommendation of one year in county jail.  States he has been unable to verify amount of credit.
DE states he has filed a grievance regarding the credit.
Atty Larimore will provide information to DA and court if more credit is found to be warranted.

Court sentences:  12 mos county jail, with credit for 72 days time served (open to modification is further information is provided at later date.)
DE must provide DNA Sample if not already provided.  Unpaid financial obligations are to be converted to Clerk of Court Collect with civil judgment.  DE to set up payplan immediately upon release from incarceration.
